4. MODS AND USER-MADE CONTENT

The Software officially supports user-made modifications through its
documented modding interface (the "Modding API"). "Mods" means original code,
content, or other materials created by you or third parties that interoperate
with the Software through the Modding API and that do not contain a
substantial portion of the Software's own code or assets.

4.1. Your Mods belong to you. Mods that consist of your original work are your
property, and Strider657 claims no ownership of them. Any portion of the
Software (code or assets) contained in, or required by, a Mod remains the
property of Strider657 and is licensed to you only as described in this
Agreement.

4.2. Mods may not be sold. You may develop and share Mods for the Software,
and we encourage it — but Mods must remain free. You may not sell Mods, charge
for access to a Mod, or lock a Mod (or any of its features or content) behind
a mandatory payment, subscription, paywall, or equivalent gate, whether inside
or outside the Software.

4.3. Voluntary support is allowed. You may accept voluntary donations and
offer general supporter memberships (for example, through Patreon, Ko-fi, or
similar platforms), including brief early-access previews of Mod updates for
supporters, provided that the Mod itself (in its current or a recent version)
always remains freely available to everyone at no charge, and that no gameplay
content or functionality of the Mod is permanently exclusive to paying
supporters.

4.4. No advertising inside Mods. Mods may not contain or inject advertising
(including ad SDKs, ad overlays, affiliate links, or sponsored placements)
into the Software.

4.5. Conduct and safety. Mods must not: redistribute the Software or any
substantial portion of its code or assets; disable, bypass, or interfere with
the Software's security, anti-cheat, or save-integrity protections beyond what
the Modding API deliberately exposes; contain malicious, deceptive, or
unlawful code or content; or collect users' data without clear disclosure and
consent.

4.6. No implied endorsement. Mods must not state or imply that they are
official, made by, or endorsed by Strider657. You may use the "Milkshake
Mania" name descriptively to indicate compatibility (for example, "a mod for
Milkshake Mania"), but you may not use the Software's name or branding as your
Mod's own primary name or branding.

4.7. Enforcement. Strider657 may remove, disable, block, or refuse to load any
Mod at any time, including for violations of this Agreement. Mods created by
third parties are used at your own risk; Strider657 is not responsible for
third-party Mods.

